[3] Utah
Date: Tue 5 Jun 2007
Source KSL.com [edited]
<http://www.ksl.com/?nid=148&sid=1311037>

Utah's Department of Health says the state has had at least one report of
_E. coli_ illness linked to ground beef that has been recalled from
Albertsons stores. Health department spokeswoman, Charla Haley, says the
man lives in Salt Lake County. He recovered without needing to be hospitalized.
Supervalu Inc announced a recall of some ground beef sold in its Albertsons
and Save-A-Lot stores because it is believed to be contaminated with _E.
coli_. Most products were sold under the Moran's label at Albertsons
stores, including some in Utah.
The recalled products had sell-by dates from 20 Apr through 7 May 2007.
